def get_hypotenuse(N: int) -> int:
    """
    Calculate the length of the hypotenuse for a right-angled triangle with the maximum possible area N.

    Parameters:
    N (int): The maximum possible area of the right-angled triangle.

    Returns:
    int: The length of the hypotenuse, rounded down to the nearest integer.
    """
    return int(2 / N ** 0.5)
